narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: the material can be confusing esp midterm 2
Course was very well-taught. Not really sure it could be improved. Kudos to Dr. Cooper for being an awesome instructor and being such a kind and helpful person.

The strengths of this course were plentiful, although this course is very content heavy, the professor teaches at a reasonable pace, and takes the time to answer all questions asks. The only weakness was that lectures were not recorded, which made it difficult if a lecture was missed.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! Taking chem off sequence was so nice because it was a much smaller class and it felt like the teaching was more tailored to our needs.
yes if it is with prof. Cooper

It's a pretty straightforward general chemistry course that prepares you well for orgo. A bit fast-paced but it's well organized and the slides are posted to help you remember the course content. If you can, take it with Dr. Cooper -- he's the best!
